snippet.textDisplay: I'm seeing so many comments from introverts who will welcome the isolation. But for me, who is an EXTREME extrovert and has an actual fear of being alone and silence, this is actually very painful and scary for me to think that this isolation will last for months. I'm ok with working from home, it gives my mind something to do. But what happens when I finish all the projects I've started and never completed? I'm going to drive my husband (who is an introvert) insane. I usually try to keep myself occupied when we are at home together until my bedtime, just so he doesn't have to engage in too much conversation with me. That's on normal days when we aren't spending all day long stuck in the house together. For now, I'm trying my best to stay out of his hair, but I'm going to crack soon. I usually unleash my extroversion on everyone else in the world, that way I'm nice and calm and quiet for my husband. I'm going to end up extremely depressed soon, I know it. I know no one cares, I just wanted to vent my frustration. Sorry.
